        public CertificateParams.Builder setIssuer(java.lang.String issuer)
        Certificate issuer. For example: /C=US/ST=California/L=Palo Alto/O=VMware, Inc. This property is not used in the input parameters when deploying an OVF package. This property will always be present in the result when retrieving information about an OVF package.
        Parameters:
        issuer - New value for the property.

      • setSubject

        public CertificateParams.Builder setSubject(java.lang.String subject)
        Certificate subject. For example: /C=US/ST=Massachusetts/L=Hopkinton/O=EMC Corporation/OU=EMC Avamar/CN=EMC Corporation. This property is not used in the input parameters when deploying an OVF package. This property will always be present in the result when retrieving information about an OVF package.
        Parameters:
        subject - New value for the property.

      • setType

        public CertificateParams.Builder setType(java.lang.String type)
        Unique identifier describing the type of the OVF parameters. The value is the name of the OVF parameters class. This property must be provided in the input parameters when deploying an OVF package. This property will always be present in the result when retrieving information about an OVF package.
